OL,3,C"That's my boy": 100-year-old reunites
OL,4,Cwith spitfire she built for World War
OL,5,CTwo
OL,7,F"Every welder has two bottles of
OL,8,Fchemical, and one of the bottles
OL,9,Fstarted swelling, and they shouted
OL,10,F'get out, get out' and we had to run
OL,11,Flike wild horses."
OL,13,F"There was workers playtime where we
OL,14,Fcould always choose a song to be
OL,15,Fplayed, and there was more welding
OL,16,Fdone in that half hour, than any other
OL,17,Ftime. We were all welding and singing.
OL,19,F"I loved it, i really loved it, like I
OL,20,Falways say everyone has a gift, and
OL,21,Fwelding is mine."
